headline: Phillips 66 CEO: Major Pipeline Project Has Broad Support
summary: US federal and state officials are lining up with the oil industry to support a plan by Phillips 66 and Kinder Morgan Inc. to deliver gasoline to California via what could become the world's largest fuel pipeline. Phillips 66 CEO Mark Lashier spoke with Romaine Bostick and Katie Greifeld about the pipeline.

headline: Phillips 66 CFO defends structure amid activist investor pressure
summary: Phillips 66 (PSX) has been under pressure from activist investor Elliott Management to split up its business and spin off parts in one of the biggest activist investor campaigns of 2025. Phillips 66 CFO Kevin Mitchell sits down with Yahoo Finance Executive Editor Brian Sozzi to defend the company's current structure and to discuss how the company is navigating the activist investor demands.
